e-sharpblue", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "University of Florida, USA, 1976", "traits": "Upright spreading bush, 1.5-2m, nearly evergreen in warm climates", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good productivity, can fruit year-round in mild climates", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 4}, {"name": "Gulf Coast", "slug": "gulf-coast", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "USDA Mississippi, USA, 1987", "traits": "Productive, hardy shrub, vigorous, good field survival", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "High productivity, reliable", "growing_notes": "EXCELLENT for Brisbane. Self-fertile (can plant solo). Hardy and easy to grow. Early season ripening. Highly recommended for beginners. Recommended by Fruit Tree Lane as top choice for Glass House Mountains/SE QLD.", "availability": "Fruit Tree Lane, major Brisbane/QLD nurseries", "sort_order": 5}, {"name": "Emerald", "slug": "emerald", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "University of Florida, USA, released 1999", "traits": "Vigorous, stout semi-erect canes, 1.5-2m, semi-evergreen", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Very high yields, maintains large berry size throughout harvest", "growing_notes": "EXCELLENT for Brisbane. Prolific production. Was backbone of Florida industry for decade. Early season. Cross-pollinate with Star, O’Neal, or Jewel. Reliable Brisbane performer. Commercial quality.", "availability": "Major Australian nurseries", "sort_order": 6}, {"name": "Star", "slug": "star", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "University of Florida, USA, patented selection", "traits": "Upright-spreading habit, good spring leaf development, attractive gray-green foliage with red stems", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Good productivity", "growing_notes": "GOOD for Brisbane. Part of Florida industry backbone. Late April/mid-May ripening in warm climates. Requires cross-pollination (O’Neal, Santa Fe, Emerald). Susceptible to Septoria leaf spot. May be marginal in warmer Brisbane areas.", "availability": "Specialty Australian nurseries", "sort_order": 7}, {"name": "O’Neal", "slug": "o-neal", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "North Carolina State University, USA, introduced 1987", "traits": "Vigorous, bushy growth habit, 1.2-1.8m, gray-green foliage with red stems", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "High yield, consistent quality throughout harvest", "growing_notes": "MARGINAL for warmest Brisbane areas. Excellent flavor. Usually first to ripen. Requires pollinator (Star compatible). May struggle in very low-chill areas but worth trying in cooler Brisbane suburbs. Can leaf poorly in insufficient chill.", "availability": "Specialty nurseries", "sort_order": 8}, {"name": "Blueberry Burst®", "slug": "blueberry-burst", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Australian bred, PlantNet Australia", "traits": "Naturally dwarfing, evergreen, compact bushy habit, 1-1.5m", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "High yield over 4-6 months", "growing_notes": "EXCELLENT for Brisbane. Australian-bred specifically for local conditions. Self-pollinating. Perfect for containers. When planted with Blueberry Kisses®, provides 6-8 months supply. Favorite at Brookfield Gardens.", "availability": "Brookfield Gardens Brisbane, PlantNet Australia stockists", "sort_order": 9}, {"name": "Blueberry Kisses®", "slug": "blueberry-kisses", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "North Carolina State University/USDA-ARS, USA, released 1978", "traits": "Vigorous, upright growth with good foliage, 2-3m height, deciduous", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Highly productive, late season", "growing_notes": "EXCELLENT for Brisbane. Australian-bred. Characterized by extra-large fruit size. Self-pollinating but best with Blueberry Burst®. Achieves