iginal cultivar names in Australian collection", "flesh_fruit": "Variable characteristics from Caribbean germplasm", "yield_notes": "Adapted to tropical/subtropical conditions", "growing_notes": "First international introduction to Australian Cassava Collection. Brought subtropical-adapted Caribbean germplasm to Queensland. Historic importance for Australian cassava development. Suitable for Brisbane climate zone with adequate moisture.", "availability": "Research collections, historical germplasm banks", "sort_order": 5}, {"name": "Thai Collection (CIAT cultivars)", "slug": "thai-collection-ciat-cultivars", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Introduced from Thailand 1974, containing CIAT cultivars plus one local Thai variety", "traits": "Asian tropical adaptation, diverse characteristics", "flesh_fruit": "High-starch varieties from major cassava-producing region", "yield_notes": "Selected for high productivity in Asian conditions", "growing_notes": "Second major international introduction to UQ collection. Brought Asian tropical germplasm adapted to monsoon conditions similar to parts of Queensland. Important genetic diversity source. Suitable for Brisbane with irrigation during dry periods.", "availability": "Research collections", "sort_order": 6}, {"name": "Nagasakiwase", "slug": "nagasakiwase", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Asian variety grown in Australian subtropics", "traits": "Unique 2 crops per year in subtropics capability", "flesh_fruit": "Good quality, improved with summer cincturing", "yield_notes": "First crop April/May, second in August. Much larger August crop with better fruit size using cincturing technique", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 7}, {"name": "ACP444", "slug": "acp444", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "origin": "Australian Cassava Products (Fielders/CSR) selection 1978-1984, Bundaberg