ty, light brown color with pleasant aroma, TSS 23°Brix", "yield_notes": "Good table variety", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 3}, {"name": "CO-3 🧬", "slug": "co-3", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "India - TNAU, hybrid: Cricket Ball × Vavivalasa", "traits": "Oblong shape, light brown fruit, suitable for high-density planting", "flesh_fruit": "Sweet taste", "yield_notes": "157 kg per tree annually, bearing from 4th year onwards", "growing_notes": "Specifically bred for high-density commercial orchards in Kerala/Tamil Nadu. Intermediate tree stature suitable for intensive planting systems. Well-adapted to tropical monsoon climate. Good for commercial Kerala cultivation where land is premium.", "availability": "Tamil Nadu and Kerala agricultural nurseries, commercial growers", "sort_order": 4}, {"name": "PKM-1 🌱", "slug": "pkm-1", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "India - Periyakulam Horticultural Research Station, Tamil Nadu, clonal selection from Guthi", "traits": "Dwarf variety, thin skin, 80g average weight", "flesh_fruit": "Buttery and very sweet pulp, rich in sugars, TSS 23°Brix", "yield_notes": "Medium-sized fruits, table purpose variety", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 5}, {"name": "PKM-2 (Hybrid 2/4) 🧬", "slug": "pkm-2-hybrid-2-4", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "India - Periyakulam, Tamil Nadu, hybrid: Guthi × Kirti Bharti", "traits": "Variable size", "flesh_fruit": "Good quality", "yield_notes": "Productive hybrid", "growing_notes": "Developed specifically for South Indian tropical conditions. Well-adapted to Kerala''s monsoon climate. Hybrid vigor provides good disease resistance and yield. Suitable for commercial cultivation in Kerala.", "availability": "Tamil Nadu and Kerala agricultural nurseries", "sort_order": 6}, {"name": "PKM-3 🧬", "slug": "pkm-3", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "India - Periyakulam, 1994 release, hybrid: Guthi × Cricket Ball", "traits": "Vertical growth habit, big-sized oval fruits, cluster-bearing habit, suitable for high-density planting", "flesh_fruit": "Good quality", "yield_notes": "14 tonnes per hectare, excellent for intensive cultivation", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 7}, {"name": "PKM-4 🌱", "slug": "pkm-4", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "India - Periyakulam, clonal selection from open-pollinated PKM-1", "traits": "Spindle-shaped fruits, suitable for dry flakes production", "flesh_fruit": "Attractive light pinkish honey-brown color, crisp and sweet, TSS 24°Brix", "yield_notes": "Excellent for processing", "growing_notes": "Developed for processing industry in tropical India. High TSS ideal for dried flakes. Well-adapted to Kerala''s tropical monsoon climate. Unique spindle shape. Good for both fresh market and processing in Kerala.", "availability": "Tamil Nadu and Kerala agricultural institutions", "sort_order": 8}, {"name": "PKM-5 🌱", "slug": "pkm-5", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "India - Periyakulam, recent selection", "traits": "Improved variety", "flesh_fruit": "Good quality", "yield_notes": "Productive", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 9}, {"name": "DHS-1 🧬", "slug": "dhs-1", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "India - University of Agricultural Sciences Dharwad, Karnataka, hybrid: Kalipatti × Cricket Ball", "traits": "Vigorous tree, round to slightly oblong fruits, 150g average weight", "flesh_fruit": "Very sweet, soft granular mellowing flesh, light orange color, TSS 26°Brix, excellent quality", "yield_notes": "High yield potential", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 10}, {"name": "DHS-2 🧬", "slug": "dhs-2", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "ori